<concept id="concept_8BD651EE8B84434CB4D6308BC6C01B79"> 
  <title>Traffic Management</title> 
  <shortdesc>The Traffic Management page lets you specify expected traffic
	 volume changes. These settings let Adobe allocate the appropriate resources to
	 ensure that your traffic can be tracked and processed in a timely manner. 
  </shortdesc> 
  <prolog> 
	 <metadata> 
		<othermeta name="solution" content="Analytics"/> 
		<othermeta name="topic" content="Admin tools"/> </metadata>
  </prolog> 
  <conbody> 
	 <p>To access 
		<wintitle>Traffic Management</wintitle>: 
	 </p> 
	 <ol id="ol_18B1458B4BF34897A118C489FF7E9ED2"> 
		<li id="li_5D3ED0B2BD6A47FF99026390D029CD44">Click 
		  <uicontrol>Analytics</uicontrol> &gt; 
		  <uicontrol>Admin</uicontrol> &gt; 
		  <uicontrol>Report Suites</uicontrol>, then select a report suite. 
		</li> 
		<li id="li_BB9B80119A1240A986B05890C49099AD">Click 
		  <uicontrol>Edit Settings</uicontrol> &gt; 
		  <uicontrol>Traffic Management</uicontrol> &gt; 
		  <i>&lt;selection&gt;</i>. 
		</li> 
	 </ol> 
  </conbody> 
</concept>
